<TITLE> JU entry tests start on Nov 2 </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Jahangirnagar University, Oct 30 (bdnews24.com)--Jahangirnagar University will hold entry tests for the first-year Bachelor's degree (honours) courses for the academic year 2009-2010 from Nov 2-14. Acting registrar Abu Bakar Siddique told bdnews24.com on Friday that 1,500 students will be admitted to 27 departments and two institutes under five faculties. Business Studies Faculty, Institute of Business Administration (IBA) and Institute of Information and Technology (IIT) have been newly introduced this year. "Approximately 94,000 forms were sold this year and 92,000 of them have been submitted," he said and added one out of every 62 applicants would get admission. Last academic year, 64,000 forms were collected and 62,938 forms were submitted for admission in 24 faculties. The seat plan of exams in the 'Ka' unit has already been on display at the university. Exams for the 'Ka' unit will be held on Nov 2-3, 'Gha' unit on Nov 4-5, 'Chha' unit on Nov 5, 'Cha' and 'Ummo' units on Nov 8. 'Kha' unit's test is on Nov 9-10 and 'Ga' unit's on Nov 11-14. The university will be taking tests for the first time in Multiple Choices Question (MCQ) format separately in each department. Information about the exam can be found at the university website www.juniv.edu. bdn
